# forbidden-words.local.example — template for the (gitignored) scripts/forbidden-words.local.
#
# The forbidden-words guard scans the tree for deployment-specific identifiers that must never be
# committed to this repo. The list is environment-specific, so it lives OUTSIDE git:
#
#   - locally: copy this file to scripts/forbidden-words.local and put your real terms in it
#   - in CI:   inject a ready alternation regex via the $FORBIDDEN_WORDS_PATTERN env var (from a secret)
#
# Format: one regex fragment per line; blank lines and #-comments are ignored; matched case-insensitively.
# Use \b...\b for whole-word matches and escape literal dots (\.) so e.g. an internal hostname matches.
#
# Only deployment-specific IDENTIFIERS go here. Generic credential shapes (private keys, PAT/token
# prefixes, AWS key ids, Grafana glc_/glsa_ tokens) are already BUILT IN to forbidden-words.sh — no
# need to list them.
#
# Examples (replace with your own — these are illustrative only):
example-customer
internal-host\.example\.com
200000000099
\bEXAMPLETAG\b
